features: 『Solution』Providing a convenient solution for changing the installing direction of 24 pin power supply cables with the 90-degree L-Turn right angle adapter.By allowing the main power cable to be installed at a 90 degree angle, builders are no longer need to wrap or fold the cable up and back over the motherboard and reduce the amount of cables needed in front of the motherboard tray.;
『Connectors』Connector A : 24 pin male, Connector B : 24 pin female;
『Compatibility』The adapters is standard 24 pin connector, so it will work with all of 24 pin ports on the motherboard;
『Parameter』Dimension(L*W*H): 52*31*18mm(2*1.2*0.7in), Gauge: premium high-performance black PCB with EVA pad, Quantity: 2pcs, Self-adhesive tape*1pcs;

『Note』The adapter was only designed for 24 pin port to improve the connection between your motherboard and PSU. Must install the adapter step by step to avoid shorting pins and motherboard damage. Please remove power cable and wait 10 seconds before installation.;

The adapter was only designed for 24 pin port to improve the connection between your motherboard and PSU. 2. Must install the adapter step by step to avoid shorting pins and motherboard damage. 3. Please remove power cable and wait 10 seconds before installation.

reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Do NOT use! Causes power instability and crashes under high loads
reviews.reviewText: Specs: Asrock Z390 Extreme 4, i9-9900k (no OC), Hyper 212 cooler, 2070 super, EVGA 850 g2 (gold) PSUA couple weeks after installing this, I'd get random hard lockups. Sometimes while gaming, sometimes while booting up, sometimes while putting it to sleep, all sorts of stuff. I started troubleshooting and could consistently cause it to crash using Prime95 (CPU stress test software). After resetting BIOS, monitoring temps, all that jazz I was really pulling my hair out trying to figure out the problem. I remembered I had added this adapter to clean up the look. I removed it and BAM all crashing went away. Something with this adapter is causing a voltage drop or some other bad power connection. DO NOT USE WITH A PERFORMANCE GAMING RIGTLDR: Looks great, love the way it cleans up cable management but CAUSES SEVERE POWER ISSUES. DO NOT USE

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Small and works well
reviews.reviewText: Does exactly what it says it does and seems to work pretty well so far. Description of A and B variant was correct, so I was able to order exactly what I needed for my RTX 4070FE. Appreciate that it’s small (unlike many other 180 degree 12VHPWR adapters)! Would work especially well in a SFF build where there’s little space for cable bends.The visual design is pretty subtle and I feel it would work well with most builds. Don’t think it needs “ATX 3.0 12VHPWR 600W 16P To 16P 180” written on the outside (I know what it is), but it doesn’t bother me too much.As seems to be standard with most adapters of this kind, there’s no clip on the GPU side. I assume this is because there wouldn’t really be room for you to physically unclip it from the GPU. Not an issue for me as it’s really snug in the GPU, but could be a concern for others. As is, just make sure it’s fully inserted when you’re done building your rig.While the adapter is working well so far, I haven’t used it for very long. Will update if there’s any issues.
